  title="Insurance claims"
  subhead="Process-literate claim support. Xactimate-ready scopes of loss. A named project manager who's done this 100+ times."
  serviceTag="insurance"
>
  <h2>What our claim support looks like</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Pre-claim inspection</strong> — before you open a claim, we'll tell you honestly if there's enough damage to justify it. A denied claim is worse than no claim.</li>
    <li><strong>Documentation packet</strong> — forty+ photos, hail/wind indicators, and a written scope of loss.</li>
    <li><strong>Adjuster meet</strong> — we show up on-site when the adjuster visits. You don't have to be there.</li>
    <li><strong>Supplemental items</strong> — if the adjuster's scope misses code-required items (new decking, ice-and-water, drip edge), we document and the carrier pays the supplement. This is normal.</li>
    <li><strong>Install + close</strong> — once the insurance scope is agreed, we install and deliver the final documentation packet for your file.</li>
  </ol>
  <h2>What we won't do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We are not a public adjuster — that's a separately-licensed role under <a href="/legal/tcpa">Tex. Ins. Code § 4102</a>. We're your contractor.</li>
    <li>We will not negotiate your claim on your behalf in a way that crosses into PA territory. We document; you (or a licensed PA you hire separately) negotiate.</li>
    <li>We will not waive or absorb your deductible. Insurance fraud, criminal exposure for both of us.</li>
  </ul>
  <h2>Carriers we work with regularly</h2>
  <p>State Farm, Allstate, USAA, Farmers, Liberty Mutual, Progressive, Nationwide, Travelers, Chubb, Texas Farm Bureau, and most TDI-regulated carriers. Each has its own Xactimate preferences — we know them.</p>
</ServiceLayout>
